# FastMoss product research

**One tool:** FastMoss only. **Do not** suggest EchoTik, Kalodata subscriptions, or dual stack.

Owner override: `data/research/course/PRODUCT_RESEARCH.md` · Setup: `docs/FOR_OWNER_FASTMOSS_SETUP.md`

## Launch path A *(now — API scout not required)*

1. Owner subscribes FastMoss (~$59/mo Basic — verify on site)
2. Owner picks **8–10 products** in FastMoss UI (ads, trend up, brand match, course filters)
3. Owner gives product names → CEO clips via `factory_cli make-clip`
4. Save/confirm list in `data/tiktok_shop/products.json`

## Launch path B *(when API wired)*

Secrets: `FASTMOSS_CLIENT_ID`, `FASTMOSS_CLIENT_SECRET` → new cloud agent run → `bash scripts/install.sh`

```bash
python3 -m shorts_bot.tiktok_shop.scout_cli status
python3 -m shorts_bot.tiktok_shop.scout_cli run --preset middle_core --limit 10
```

Until scout ships, `scout_cli run` may error with “not wired” — **that is expected**; use path A.

## Module 3 quality bar (FastMoss)

| Check | Why |
|-------|-----|
| Ad badges / paid top videos | Brand invests — easier to convert |
| Revenue trend **up** | Avoid dying products |
| Brand match | Image, title, shop align |
| Commission $ | Price × rate worth posting |
| Creator mix | Not only brand self-promo |

Presets `middle_core` / `two_hundred` are **legacy bot names** — apply equivalent filters in FastMoss UI.

## Delegate

`/product-research` → **`product-researcher`** (background). CEO carries picks forward — subagents have no chat memory.

## Budget

FastMoss ~$59/mo vs retired EchoTik ~$125 — see `docs/LAUNCH_BUDGET.md`. **Do not pay EchoTik.**
